706522f-b.title: Brooklyn: Rockaway Parkway - Avenue K
706522f-b.text:
(1)
Rockaway Parkway, adjoining the N.E. corner of Ave. E, showing
the home of Will Warners, upon whose place, in the summer of 1922, E.
Lyle's outfit housed its "Wild West Show.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, showing the barns.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

706521f-a.title: Brooklyn: Rockaway Parkway - Avenue K
706521f-a.text:
(1)
1663 Rockaway Parkway, east side, north of Ave. E, showing the G. Des-
rault house, (1873); later the William Warner house. IIn the street are
trolley tracks of the B.R.T. Co.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, after raising and grading of street.
July 27, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
